parameters: \N<Yuia>Is this the place... where my mother and Seno might be...
\N<Yuia>Excuse me, soldier sir. May I have a moment of your time?
\N<Luda Soldier>What is it? Make it quick.

\N<Yuia>Um... have two women been brought here recently? They are of
marriageable age and quite attractive...
\N<Luda Soldier>Huh? Why do you ask such a thing?
\N<Yuia>Please don't be suspicious, the truth is that...

\N<Luda Soldier>...don't tell me those women are your relatives? You've come
to take them back?

\N<Yuia>No, no. It's rather embarrassing to say, but a few days ago,
I heard from my companions that they saw such women here.

\N<Yuia>If they are as beautiful as they say... I was hoping I might
be fortunate enough to receive some of your leftovers by
coming here.
\N<Luda Soldier>Hmph, so that's what it is, you scoundrel.
\N<Yuia>...

\N<Luda Soldier>Indeed, there seem to have been such women, but I don't know
the details. Perhaps they're mistresses of a high-ranking
officer? That's not something a non-commissioned officer
like me would know.
\N<Yuia>Is that so... That's unfortunate.
\N<Luda Soldier>Now that you know, get out of here quickly.
\N<??>...damn! ...ing around!
\N<Yuia>Hm...?
\N<Luda Soldier>Tch... not again, these guys never learn.
\N<Yuia>What's going on...? Is it a quarrel between soldiers...?
\N<Yuia>If I may be so bold, are you hurt?
\N<Hebeta>I'm fine... it's the usual, I'm used to it.

\N<Yuia>Why... why do your fellow Luda soldiers do such terrible
things to each other?
\N<Hebeta>More importantly... who are you?

\N<Yuia>My apologies, I am from a nearby village. I came here to
deliver tributes to the Luda soldiers.
\N<Hebeta>Huh...

\N<Hebeta>According to them, they just can't stand my ugly face. It
makes them nauseous, ruins their appetite.
\N<Yuia>Just for that reason, they treat you so terribly...?
\N<Hebeta>Seems so. Well, I'm used to it...
\N<Yuia>...
\N<Yuia>What to do...? Should I stay here?

\N<Yuia>Mother and Seno, there seems to be no mistake that people
like them were here, but I don't know the details or their
whereabouts. Can I really obtain any useful information
about them by staying here any longer...

\N<Yuia>No... I can always return to the city later. For now, it
might be best to stay here a while longer and search for
their whereabouts...

\N<Luda Soldier>That's what I keep telling you! Don't show your filthy face
in front of us!
\N<Hebeta>So-sorry... I'm sorry for being like this...
\N<Luda Soldier>Tch...!
\N<Yuia>Excuse me, are you... alright?
\N<Hebeta>Oh, the person from yesterday? You're still here?

\N<Yuia>Why... why do you endure such treatment and still stay with
Luda?
\N<Hebeta>Eh...?

\N<Yuia>Meeting you here must be some sort of fate. Would you mind
telling me your reasons?

\N<Hebeta>...It's not a big reason, you see, I just want to get
married.
\N<Yuia>Marriage...?
\N<Hebeta>Yes, are you married?
\N<Yuia>I am...

\N<Hebeta>No need to say it. You have a well-featured face, so you
must be. If only I were born with a face as well-featured as
yours.

\N<Hebeta>You see... I've never been favored by women. Because of this
ugly face.
\N<Yuia>...

\N<Hebeta>Still... I want to spend my life with someone I love. Isn't
it okay to dream at least that much?
\N<Hebeta>That's why... I'm here.

\N<Hebeta>Isn't staying here the best way for someone like me, who's
like an insect, to become somewhat equal to women? That's
why I can stay here, no matter what happens to me.
\N<Yuia>...
A
